metadata.name: Collectible Ford Mustang Fastback (1967)
metadata.description: 1967 Mustang has changed a lot: now it was a real sports car in the American version. The initiator of the restyling was Lee Iacocca again, who instructed the designers to make the model more prestigious, comfortable and dynamic. In total, Ford produced over 225,000 Wimbledon White examples and around 187,000 Fastback Mustangs making a Wimbledon White Fastback model one of the most popular Mustangs of the first generation.
